I have an object returned to me from third-party API. Object has following structure:
`object = {
    _links: ...
}`

When I'm trying to access `_links` object using dot-notation like this: `object._links` I've got `no-underscore-dangle` error while trying to get object property with brakets `object['_links']` leads to `dot-notation` error. How to deal with such rules confusion?

I am getting the alert, that I have to validate in prop types match, but I think it is not necessary.

import React from 'react';

```javascript
const Header = (props) => {
  const { match } = props; // 'match' is missing props validation (react/prop-types)
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Hello</h1>
      <h3>ID: {match.params.id}</h3>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Header;
```

Do I need to validate it? What's the new convention?

